
[1]reveal

   REVE'AL, v.t. [L. revelo; re and velo, to veil.]

   1. To disclose; to discover; to show; to make known something before
   unknown or concealed; as, to reveal secrets.

   2. To disclose, discover or make known from heaven. God has been
   pleased to reveal his will to man.

   The wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and
   unrighteousness of men. Romans 1.

             REVE'AL, n. A revealing; disclosure. [Not in use.]
